<br>
We choose mods so <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">they</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> can make these decisions.  I really don't feel it is up to the board to decide on all things.  We choose mods we feel have the ability to make the choice that is right for the integrity of the forum.<br>
<br>
I have seen mods bitching about people yelling at them, disliking their decisions, what have you, to that I say tough shit.  It is the job of a mod to make the right choice for the forum, and it is the right of some people to complain about that.  Some people bitching and whining about things should not effect the decisions you make or how you make them.   <br>
<br>
Take Ixi for example, it was right to ban him, he should have been banned long before he actually was and there was no reason to adopt a rule we really didn't need and can't enforce in order to justify banning him.  It is right to ban SZ flamers and spammers, you don't need some obscure rule, to justify it.<br>
<br>
My advice for our new mods, do your jobs, use common sense and just ignore the pissy whiners who think this is democracy.  It is your job <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">not</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> to be affected by those people.  We have nominated people who have a really good feel for what the forum wants as a community and what the forum needs to function smoothly.  You can listen to and consider the populus' needs, but it doesn't mean you are ruled by them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub228.ezboard.com/bxevserverboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=usildordhujata>Usildor Dhujata</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Crypt Pimp</span><br>  Posts: 1185<br> <font color=#330000>(11/12/03 1:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub228.ezboard.com/fxevserverboardsfrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1132.topic&index=45>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/poeticsarcasm/images/marblemn.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Position</span><hr size=1> I think what I said has been minsinterpreted.  I didnt say the board makes all the decisions.  I said it COULD be put to a vote by the whole board if there is a large disagreement with a decision and the mods themselves don't agree with it.  We pick the mods, and as such if there's a huge issue, we should be able to overturn their decision.  I did not mean this as something that should be used repeatedly.  But just in the instance of a big major bitch fest (I dont mean five or ten jackasses not liking something.) <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
